{'content_type': 'audio_transcription', 'text': "Yeah, absolutely. That all makes a lot of sense. I think what you're describing is really that you want to build a kind of trusted ecosystem that people actually want to use because it's valuable to them. And it makes total sense to integrate it into an onboarding flow or make it like a yearly check-in rather than just something they do once and forget about. That way, it feels like a natural part of being in the community.

As for whether it needs to be an app or not, I think you can start simple. It could just be a web-based platform that they can easily access from their phone or computer. You don't necessarily have to build a full-on mobile app unless you really want to. And in terms of what you ask people, I think it's about striking that balance between structure and flexibility. You can have some core questions that really matter—like key skills, areas of expertise, and availability—but also leave room for people to share a bit of their personality or unique approaches. That way it feels a bit more human and less like just filling out a form.

Overall, the idea is to weave it into the culture of the community so that it becomes this living resource—something people know they can rely on when they need it, and something they feel good about contributing to. So yeah, we can definitely brainstorm more on making it both useful and a good experience for everyone.", 'direction': 'out', 'decoding_id': None}
